bottlebrush
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:an Aust. shrub with dense, coloured flower heads consisting of stamens all around the stem; usu. in NZ applied to the introduced Aust. genus <i>Callistemon</i> [or the Myrtaceae or Protaceae families] used as ornamentals, with brilliant red flowers reminiscent in shape to the brushes used to clean out (?orig. wine) bottles [cf the similar decriptive application to <i>pohutukawa</i>
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
